# Security Rules (Enforced)

This is a DeFi application managing real funds. Security violations are blocking.

## Forbidden Practices

### Rust
- Calling `.unwrap()` on user-derived data or external input
- Logging private keys, seed phrases, or raw key bytes
- Storing keys anywhere except OS keychain
- Using `unsafe` blocks without a documented safety proof
- Rolling custom cryptography implementations
- Executing system commands with user-provided arguments

### TypeScript
- Dynamic code evaluation in any form
- Rendering unsanitized HTML content
- Using the `any` type — use `unknown` with type guards instead
- Storing keys, seeds, or mnemonics in JS variables, browser storage, or cookies
- Making HTTP requests with unvalidated user-supplied URLs

### Both Languages
- Hardcoded secrets, API keys, RPC endpoints, or private keys
- Disabling security lints or lint rules
- Adding dependencies with known CVEs
- Logging user financial data (balances, positions, trade amounts) in production

## Required Patterns

- All Tauri commands validate inputs on the Rust side
- All blockchain amounts use checked arithmetic (`checked_add`, `checked_mul` in Rust; BigInt in TS)
- All user-facing errors are generic — no internal state leakage
- Transaction execution requires simulation first
- Background automation respects spending limits and stop-loss guardrails
